info.name: Classic API
info.description:
This collection is designed to provide an overview of how to use the Jamf Pro Classic API. 

* All GET requests should include an example response.
* ALL POST requests should include a pre-populated request body.
	* Although required fields cannot easily be noted in Postman, the required fields for creating a specific object will always be included in the pre-populated response body.
	* Check the [Jamf Developer Portal](https://developer.jamf.com) for more information about required fields.
* Some endpoints may include more than one example request/response.
	* These examples should help indicate how to use dynamic request/response bodies for endpoints that have additional fields condional upon values of other fields (e.g. An LDAP Jamf Pro Account will include or require information about the LDAP server, whereas a standar account does not)
	* Issuance of commands for mobile devices and computers has extensive examples, demonstrating all of the available commands and the supported fields associated with those specific commands.

item.name: accounts
Finds all accounts

header.value: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0, post-check=0, pre-check=0

item.name: Finds a subset of hardware/software reports by computer UDID

variable.description: Range must be specified in the following format: yyyy-mm-dd_yyyy-mm-dd
Supported values include: Software, Hardware, Fonts, Plugins

request.description: Subset values can also be appended using an ampersand to return multiple subsets (e.g. /subsets/Software&Hardware)

response.name: Finds a subset of hardware/software reports by computer UDID

variable.description: Range must be specified in the following format: yyyy-mm-dd_yyyy-mm-dd

        <self_service_description>This math textbook is written by a Middle School Special Education Teacher who wanted to give her students a new and easy way to understand and learn math. &#xa0;This interactive book features videos made by the teacher, interactive practice problems and mini progress checks. &#xa0;It was written to be used in conjunction with other educational material as well. &#xa0;I have not supplied answers to every practice set, as the intention is that the practice problems would be done with the teacher in a guided, we do together type teaching model. &#xa0;Many pages feature widgets that will encourage engagement with the textbook and promote different learning styles. &#xa0;This book is intended to be used to help students who struggle with math and need to grow in their skills quickly. &#xa0;This book covers most of Nebraska's state standards, but not all of them.</self_service_description>

    <self_service>
        <install_button_text>Install</install_button_text>
        <self_service_description>Minesweeper, a refreshingly clean, yet authentic interpretation of the classic strategy/puzzle game. The object of the game is to identify all mine squares by revealing all non-mine squares. The best minesweeper experience available.

FEATURES
- Beginner size preset (upgrade to the full version for five popular presets and custom)
- Save, load, and replay games.
- Mouse path is tracked with replay, and can be displayed.
- Window can be resized at any time
- Area is always opened on the first click.
- Double-click or press both buttons to reveal adjacent squares.
- A Right-click anywhere after a game, or click the clock to start a new game.
- Best times are tracked in a high score table.
- Chording is available for faster play.
- The Inspector tool shows live game statistics.
- Colors can be changed.

NOTICE
A mouse with two separate buttons is ideal for this game. If you use a trackpad or magic mouse, be sure to enable secondary clicks in your system preferences.</self_service_description>

• Quote comments in one tap
• Exclude posts based on keywords
• “Hide All / Hide Read” comments with one tap
• Easily identify which comments are made by the Post author

Existing Alien Blue users: this is still the same Alien Blue with the same developer you know and (hopefully) love, just 100% more official! You’ll want to transfer your settings from the old client using the option in Settings/Advanced Settings/Privacy Settings/Export Settings, then Import them into this app.

• Use night mode for easy reading in the dark
• Be notified of new messages from your reddit inbox
• View websites using the integrated "Readability" reader from Arc90
• Switch between multiple reddit accounts easily
• Browse in Gallery mode (formerly Canvas)

• Upload images directly to Imgur when posting or commenting
• Expand all images in the comments with one tap
• Quote comments in one tap
• Exclude posts based on keywords
• “Hide All / Hide Read” comments with one tap
• Easily identify which comments are made by the Post author

Existing Alien Blue users: this is still the same Alien Blue with the same developer you know and (hopefully) love, just 100% more official! You’ll want to transfer your settings from the old client using the option in Settings/Advanced Settings/Privacy Settings/Export Settings, then Import them into this app.

	<name>Sample Group</name>
	<is_smart>true</is_smart>
	<criteria>
		<criterion>
			<name>Last Inventory Update</name>
			<priority>0</priority>
			<and_or>and</and_or>
			<search_type>more than x days ago</search_type>
			<value>7</value>
			<opening_paren>false</opening_paren>
			<closing_paren>false</closing_paren>
		</criterion>
	</criteria>
	<site>
		<id>-1</id>
		<name>None</name>
	</site>
</mobile_device_group>
